main event: Multiple sightings of two orb-sized objects, resembling beach balls stacked on top of each other, observed in Santa Monica, California on 8/29 at 0550Z.
interesting points: The objects were described as silvery but shifted to a reddish color.
Observation lasted for several minutes with both military and civilian sources witnessing the event.
Venus and Jupiter were mentioned in the comments regarding the sighting.
The top object occasionally drifted to the left and then returned to its position over the lower object.
Several reliable civilian witnesses reported the sighting from different locations around Santa Monica.
sighted object: Two orb-sized objects resembling beach balls stacked on top of each other
